repnme.cdata!:
Morocco - Financial Markets Development
            Loan Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The overall outcome of the project was
            rated satisfactory. The key lessons learned through the
            project are the following: 1) A continuous long-term
            partnership with the Government pays off. The Bank should
            continue with this approach for future operations on
            contractual savings which deepen already initiated reforms.
            2) However, the Bank needs to be more realistic in the
            assessment of the feasibility of certain policy measures.
            For instance, the privatization program that was initially
            foreseen as part of this project conditions was too
            ambitious, probably because of insufficient financial and
            institutional analysis and/or of an optimistic assessment of
            the political constraints on privatization. A more rigorous
            approach would require a careful assessment of the different
            constraints and risks for each measure included in the loan.

repnme.cdata!:
Morocco - Financial Markets Development
            Loan Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The Financial Markets Development Loan
            will support a program of reforms in the financial sector
            and finance the temporary cost to the Moroccan Treasury of
            implementing this program. Beyond a transitional period of
            three years, the budgetary impact will remain limited to
            about 0.17 percent of GDP per year and, therefore,
            consistent with macrostabilization objectives. The specific
            policy measures concern: 1) the reform of Treasury financing
            including the removal of mandatory placement ratios for
            banks in Treasury bonds at below market rates; 2) indirect
            monetary control including the liberalization of lending
            rates; 3) the development of capital markets; and 4) the
            banking system, in particular the privatization of the
            remaining state-owned banks and the establishment of an
            interbank foreign exchange market together with related
            prudential measures. A policy matrix details the specific
            actions to be supported by the Loan and shows how they
            complement those already implemented.
